title.narrative: By the end of 2019, health facilities and Community Health Workers have equipment, inputs and skills to provide maternal andneonatal health care.

description.narrative: UNICEF significantly improved the access to and the quality of maternal and newborn care and services through provision of equipment and strengthening of health workers' knowledge and skills. In 2019, the number of health facilities offering basic and comprehensive emergency obstetric and neonatal care reached 576 (42 per cent of total health facilities) against 546 in 2018. In 2019, 1,196 health facilities (87.5 per cent of health facilities) were offering delivery services with functional newborn resuscitation equipment, exceeding the CPD target of 329. As a result, 565,581 live births (63.8%) were assisted. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
